Spoon sorbet into large bowl. Stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping until well blended. Spoon into crust. Place in freezer 15 minutes or until slightly set. Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until smooth. (Mixture will be thick.) Immediately stir in all but 1 cup of the remaining whipped topping. Gently spoon pudding mixture over sorbet layer in crust. Freeze 4 hours or overnight. Let stand at room temperature or in refrigerator 15 minutes before serving. Garnish with remaining 1 cup whipped topping.